Think about what you actually do and don't notice in day-to-day life, and most importantly, how those things make you feel. Imagery is one of the easiest ways to play with tone and mood, so use it for that. Let us know the thing is there if it's important to the scene, and then describe it in a way that helps us know how we should feel. For instance, a sharp, clean table is more intimidating than an old worn one. If your character is meeting some authority figure who should be intimidating, describing the table with reference to how clean it is might be useful.
